Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1/2}(peeled and chopped). Chop half (double for
4p) into small pieces.

Zest half the @lemon{1/2} (double for 4p). Cut in half. Roughly chop
@parsley{5%g}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Trim the @courgette{1} and slice into 1cm rounds. Quarter the
@cherry tomatoes{125%g}.

In a #large bowl{}, mix the lemon zest, @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and
@oil{1%tbsp} (double for 4p).

Add the @salmon{200%g}. Turn to coat and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

== Bulgur Wheat ==

Place a #medium pot{} over medium heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the chopped onion and cook until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir often.

Add @water{240%ml} (double for 4p), stir in the @vegetable stock{1%sachet} and
bring to the boil.

Stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for
~{1%minute}.

Cover the #pot{} and remove from the heat. Leave aside for ~{12-15%minutes} or
until ready to serve.

== Courgette ==

Place a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (no oil).

When hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn only
every so often—this will allow the courgette to pick up a nice colour.

Once cooked, season with salt and pepper.

Transfer half the charred courgette to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Chop the remaining courgette into small pieces and set aside.

== Salmon ==

Return the (now empty) pan to high heat.

Once hot, carefully place your salmon into the pan, skin-side down.

Spoon over any remaining oil from the bowl.

Cook for ~{4-5%minutes} then turn over and cook for ~{3-4%minutes} on the other
side.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

> TIP: To get crispy skin on the fish don't move it around when it's cooking
> skin-side down.

== Herby Dressing ==

Meanwhile, to a #small bowl{} add @oil{1 1/2%tbsp} (double for 4p), a squeeze of
lemon juice and half the parsley.

Season with salt and pepper.

Mix well and set aside.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the bulgur with a #fork{}.

Stir through the tomatoes, chopped courgette, remaining parsley and a small
squeeze of lemon juice.

Share the bulgur between your plates, then top with the charred courgette
rounds and crispy salmon.

Taste and season with salt, pepper and more lemon juice if needed.

Drizzle over the herby dressing to finish.